        <name>8.2.1.2 Example determinant and inverse matrix</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h4 class="HELM_example"&gt;Example&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the matrix &lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[A=\left[\begin{array}{rr}2&amp;amp;3\\ 1&amp;amp;-2\end{array}\right]\]&lt;/span&gt; find its determinant. What does this tell you about &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(A^{-1}\)&lt;/span&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[|A|=2\times (-2)-1\times 3=-7.\]&lt;/span&gt; Since &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(|A|\neq 0\)&lt;/span&gt; then &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(A^{-1}\)&lt;/span&gt; exists. Therefore, we can now find &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(A^{-1}\):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[A^{-1}=\dfrac{1}{(-7)}\left[\begin{array}{rr}-2&amp;amp;-3\\
-1&amp;amp;2\end{array}\right]=\dfrac{1}{7}\left[\begin{array}{rr}2&amp;amp;3\\ 1&amp;amp;-2\end{array}\right]\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
